contentment : Madonna and child. The use of dark, subdued colors on Mary's clothing make me feel calm, as do the subject's facial expressions. The shadows and dark green lining of her cloak give the illusion of 3 dimensions. The subjects are placed within the Golden Mean--Mary to the right and Jesus on the left, and her circling hands tie the piece together. I wonder what Jesus is looking at off to the left. The skin tones look jaundiced, and should be paler, but the lights and shadows on them are accurate. The fingers touching Jesus don't make any imprints, and this is not realistic, especially on a fat baby which would dimple easily. Another thing I find confusing is Mary's sleeve, which shows far too much embroidered detail for a poor woman who rode a donkey and gave birth in a stable. The landscape looks to be somewhere pines grow (northern Italy?) Overall, a very peaceful work of art.
